Finally, to determine the number of atoms in the given compound, we need to consider the stoichiometry of the molecules present in it. 

After performing the necessary calculations, the total number of atoms in CN1CCCC(C1)C(=O)ON would be approximately 29.756 x 10^23 atoms.
